{"title":"Extras Config - Stencil","description":"Extras Config","url":"/docs/config-extras","contributors":["mattdsteele","itsravenous","kensodemann","peterpeterparker","adamdbradley","rtpHarry"],"lastUpdated":"2020-12-17T17:13:55Z","headings":[{"id":"extras","level":1,"text":"Extras"},{"id":"appendchildslotfix","level":3,"text":"appendChildSlotFix"},{"id":"clonenodefix","level":3,"text":"cloneNodeFix"},{"id":"cssvarsshim","level":3,"text":"cssVarsShim"},{"id":"dynamicimportshim","level":3,"text":"dynamicImportShim"},{"id":"lifecycledomevents","level":3,"text":"lifecycleDOMEvents"},{"id":"safari10","level":3,"text":"safari10"},{"id":"scriptdataopts","level":3,"text":"scriptDataOpts"},{"id":"shadowdomshim","level":3,"text":"shadowDomShim"},{"id":"slotchildnodesfix","level":3,"text":"slotChildNodesFix"}],"srcPath":"./src/docs/config/extras.md","hypertext":["div",null,["h1",{"id":"extras"},"\n  \n  Extras\n  \n"],"\n",["p",null,"The ",["code",null,"extras"]," config contains options to add and remove runtime for DOM features that require manipulations to polyfills. For example, not all DOM APIs are fully polyfilled when using the Slot polyfill. Most of these are opt-in, since not all users require the additional runtime."],"\n",["p",null,"By default, Stencil does not work on IE11, Edge 18 and below (Edge before it moved to Chromium) and Safari 10. In order to support legacy browsers, the browsers would need to download and run polyfills. By using the ",["code",null,"extras"]," config, apps can opt-in these additional runtime settings."],"\n",["p",null,"Example ",["code",null,"extras"]," config when ",["strong",null,"supporting"]," legacy browsers:"],"\n\n  ",["highlight-code",null,"\n    ",["pre",{"class":"language-tsx"},["code",{"class":"language-tsx"},["span",{"class":"token keyword"},"export"]," ",["span",{"class":"token keyword"},"const"]," config",["span",{"class":"token operator"},":"]," Config ",["span",{"class":"token operator"},"="]," ",["span",{"class":"token punctuation"},"{"],"\n  buildEs5",["span",{"class":"token operator"},":"]," ",["span",{"class":"token string"},"'prod'"],["span",{"class":"token punctuation"},","],"\n  extras",["span",{"class":"token operator"},":"]," ",["span",{"class":"token punctuation"},"{"],"\n    cssVarsShim",["span",{"class":"token operator"},":"]," ",["span",{"class":"token boolean"},"true"],["span",{"class":"token punctuation"},","],"\n    dynamicImportShim",["span",{"class":"token operator"},":"]," ",["span",{"class":"token boolean"},"true"],["span",{"class":"token punctuation"},","],"\n    shadowDomShim",["span",{"class":"token operator"},":"]," ",["span",{"class":"token boolean"},"true"],["span",{"class":"token punctuation"},","],"\n    safari10",["span",{"class":"token operator"},":"]," ",["span",{"class":"token boolean"},"true"],["span",{"class":"token punctuation"},","],"\n    scriptDataOpts",["span",{"class":"token operator"},":"]," ",["span",{"class":"token boolean"},"true"],["span",{"class":"token punctuation"},","],"\n    appendChildSlotFix",["span",{"class":"token operator"},":"]," ",["span",{"class":"token boolean"},"false"],["span",{"class":"token punctuation"},","],"\n    cloneNodeFix",["span",{"class":"token operator"},":"]," ",["span",{"class":"token boolean"},"false"],["span",{"class":"token punctuation"},","],"\n    slotChildNodesFix",["span",{"class":"token operator"},":"]," ",["span",{"class":"token boolean"},"true"],["span",{"class":"token punctuation"},","],"\n  ",["span",{"class":"token punctuation"},"}"],"\n",["span",{"class":"token punctuation"},"}"],["span",{"class":"token punctuation"},";"]]],"\n  "],"\n  ",["p",null,"Note: ",["code",null,"buildEs5: 'prod'"]," was also set in the config since this example needs to support legacy browsers. See the ",["a",{"href":"/docs/config#buildes5"},"buildEs5 config"]," for more information."],"\n\n",["h3",{"id":"appendchildslotfix"},"\n  ",["a",{"class":"heading-link","href":"#appendchildslotfix"},["app-icon",{"name":"link"}],"\n  appendChildSlotFix\n  "],"\n"],"\n",["p",null,"By default, the slot polyfill does not update ",["code",null,"appendChild()"]," so that it appends new child nodes into the correct child slot like how shadow dom works. This is an opt-in polyfill for those who need it."],"\n\n",["h3",{"id":"clonenodefix"},"\n  ",["a",{"class":"heading-link","href":"#clonenodefix"},["app-icon",{"name":"link"}],"\n  cloneNodeFix\n  "],"\n"],"\n",["p",null,"By default, the runtime does not polyfill ",["code",null,"cloneNode()"]," when cloning a component that uses the slot polyfill. This is an opt-in polyfill for those who need it."],"\n\n",["h3",{"id":"cssvarsshim"},"\n  ",["a",{"class":"heading-link","href":"#cssvarsshim"},["app-icon",{"name":"link"}],"\n  cssVarsShim\n  "],"\n"],"\n",["p",null,"Include the CSS Custom Property polyfill/shim for legacy browsers."],"\n",["p",null,"A result of this being set to ",["code",null,"false"]," is that you will need to manually provide \"fallback\" properties to legacy builds. For example, in the css below, the css variable will not be polyfilled for IE11, so the developer will manually need to provide a fallback just before the css variable. If the app does not need to support IE11 it's recommended to leave ",["code",null,"cssVarsShim"]," set to the default value of ",["code",null,"false"],"."],"\n\n  ",["highlight-code",null,"\n    ",["pre",{"class":"language-css"},["code",{"class":"language-css"},["span",{"class":"token selector"},"div"]," ",["span",{"class":"token punctuation"},"{"],"\n  ",["span",{"class":"token property"},"color"],["span",{"class":"token punctuation"},":"]," blue",["span",{"class":"token punctuation"},";"]," ",["span",{"class":"token comment"},"/* Used by IE */"],"\n  ",["span",{"class":"token property"},"color"],["span",{"class":"token punctuation"},":"]," ",["span",{"class":"token function"},"var"],["span",{"class":"token punctuation"},"("],"--color",["span",{"class":"token punctuation"},")"],["span",{"class":"token punctuation"},";"]," ",["span",{"class":"token comment"},"/* Used by modern browsers */"],"\n",["span",{"class":"token punctuation"},"}"]]],"\n  "],"\n  \n",["h3",{"id":"dynamicimportshim"},"\n  ",["a",{"class":"heading-link","href":"#dynamicimportshim"},["app-icon",{"name":"link"}],"\n  dynamicImportShim\n  "],"\n"],"\n",["p",null,"Dynamic ",["code",null,"import()"]," shim. This is only needed for Edge 18 and below, and Firefox 67 and below. If you do not need to support Edge 18 and below (Edge before it moved to Chromium) then it's recommended to set ",["code",null,"dynamicImportShim"]," to ",["code",null,"false"],". Defaults to ",["code",null,"false"],"."],"\n\n",["h3",{"id":"lifecycledomevents"},"\n  ",["a",{"class":"heading-link","href":"#lifecycledomevents"},["app-icon",{"name":"link"}],"\n  lifecycleDOMEvents\n  "],"\n"],"\n",["p",null,"Dispatches component lifecycle events. By default these events are not dispatched, but by enabling this to ",["code",null,"true"]," these events can be listened for on ",["code",null,"window"],". Mainly used for testing."],"\n",["table",null,"\n",["thead",null,"\n",["tr",null,"\n",["th",null,"Event Name"],"\n",["th",null,"Description"],"\n"],"\n"],"\n",["tbody",null,["tr",null,"\n",["td",null,["code",null,"stencil_componentWillLoad"]],"\n",["td",null,"Dispatched for each component's ",["code",null,"componentWillLoad"],"."],"\n"],"\n",["tr",null,"\n",["td",null,["code",null,"stencil_componentWillUpdate"]],"\n",["td",null,"Dispatched for each component's ",["code",null,"componentWillUpdate"],"."],"\n"],"\n",["tr",null,"\n",["td",null,["code",null,"stencil_componentWillRender"]],"\n",["td",null,"Dispatched for each component's ",["code",null,"componentWillRender"],"."],"\n"],"\n",["tr",null,"\n",["td",null,["code",null,"stencil_componentDidLoad"]],"\n",["td",null,"Dispatched for each component's ",["code",null,"componentDidLoad"],"."],"\n"],"\n",["tr",null,"\n",["td",null,["code",null,"stencil_componentDidUpdate"]],"\n",["td",null,"Dispatched for each component's ",["code",null,"componentDidUpdate"],"."],"\n"],"\n",["tr",null,"\n",["td",null,["code",null,"stencil_componentDidRender"]],"\n",["td",null,"Dispatched for each component's ",["code",null,"componentDidRender"],"."],"\n"],"\n"]],"\n\n",["h3",{"id":"safari10"},"\n  ",["a",{"class":"heading-link","href":"#safari10"},["app-icon",{"name":"link"}],"\n  safari10\n  "],"\n"],"\n",["p",null,"Safari 10 supports ES modules with ",["code",null,"<script type=\"module\">"],", however, it did not implement ",["code",null,"<script nomodule>"],". When set ",["code",null,"safari10"]," is set to ",["code",null,"false"],", the runtime will not patch support for Safari 10. If the app does not need to support Safari 10, it's recommended to set this to ",["code",null,"false"],". Defaults to ",["code",null,"false"],"."],"\n\n",["h3",{"id":"scriptdataopts"},"\n  ",["a",{"class":"heading-link","href":"#scriptdataopts"},["app-icon",{"name":"link"}],"\n  scriptDataOpts\n  "],"\n"],"\n",["p",null,"It is possible to assign data to the actual ",["code",null,"<script>"]," element's ",["code",null,"data-opts"]," property, which then gets passed to Stencil's initial bootstrap. This feature is only required for very special cases and rarely needed. When set to ",["code",null,"false"]," it will not read this data. Defaults to ",["code",null,"false"],"."],"\n\n",["h3",{"id":"shadowdomshim"},"\n  ",["a",{"class":"heading-link","href":"#shadowdomshim"},["app-icon",{"name":"link"}],"\n  shadowDomShim\n  "],"\n"],"\n",["p",null,"If enabled ",["code",null,"true"],", the runtime will check if the shadow dom shim is required. However, if it's determined that shadow dom is already natively supported by the browser then it does not request the shim. Setting to ",["code",null,"false"]," will avoid all shadow dom tests. If the app does not need to support IE11 or Edge 18 and below, it's recommended to set ",["code",null,"shadowDomShim"]," to ",["code",null,"false"],". Defaults to ",["code",null,"false"],"."],"\n\n",["h3",{"id":"slotchildnodesfix"},"\n  ",["a",{"class":"heading-link","href":"#slotchildnodesfix"},["app-icon",{"name":"link"}],"\n  slotChildNodesFix\n  "],"\n"],"\n",["p",null,"For browsers that do not support shadow dom (IE11 and Edge 18 and below), slot is polyfilled to simulate the same behavior. However, the host element's ",["code",null,"childNodes"]," and ",["code",null,"children"]," getters are not patched to only show the child nodes and elements of the default slot. Defaults to ",["code",null,"false"],"."]]}